ListTitle="The Program"
DescriptionTitle="The Program"
DescriptionEntry="The Program, seemingly led by the illusive Dr. Hadley, are an offshoot of XCOM, branching off in the 1970's. In the original invasion, they sent a single operative and Dr. Hadley to assist, which proved instrumental to the war effort, but when the base was lost, those personnel went MIA. In the time since, little has escaped; even now, the Program goes unnamed, and details related to the organization remain frighteningly obscure. What is evident is that their primary focus is ensuring that when ADVENT falls, they- at the expense of any other, even XCOM- stand on top of the pile of rubble. In other words, be careful when dealing with them. Their technology is advanced, and their operatives elite, but they are not on your side, Commander, and your goals may not always align."

[FactionProgramOperatives X2EncyclopediaTemplate]
ListTitle="Program Operatives"
DescriptionTitle="Program Soldier Classes"
DescriptionEntry="The Program fields a small number of psionic operatives. Augmented cybernetically and genetically through a substance known as \"MELD\", they are truly elite, each a veteran of twenty, thirty, or even forty years of combat against both human and alien threats. Each has a unique skillset, but they share a common base of psionic abilities, such as Mind Control, Mind Wrack, and Mind Meld."

[FactionProgramFavors X2EncyclopediaTemplate]
ListTitle="Program Support"
DescriptionTitle="One Small Favor"
DescriptionEntry="The Program can spare enough time to send one of their squads in the place of XCOM's once per month. Doing so will help build your relationship with them, eventually increasing your influence with them and unlocking new Resistance Orders. If a favor is a available, a white checkbox will be present above the mission launch button. Checking it will call in the favor. Note that favors cannot be called in on narrative missions."

